node.text:
Hope everyone had a good weekend💗 Feels like I’ve been totally off since yesterday, like I said on my story my cat finally had her kittens and I’ve been consumed 🥺 The birth story is quite funny, when I realised that my cat was about to give birth, I panicked and called Filippa. She came over and helped me, but after the second kitten came out I had to run to the bathroom and throw up😅 Watching a cat give birth is not for people with a weak stomach. Anyways, the mum is doing fine and all her 5(!!!) kittens are also doing great🥺 Swipe for a first sneak peek of my chinchilla persian babies💗
Wearing @fitjeans in the first pic 👖🥰

node.text: Wearing the ”animal collection” from @beaybl , available in several different colors(swipe to see some of my favorites)💪🏽 Soon off to the gym for a legday, going to focus a lot on my deadlifts today, worked my way up from 60 kgs to 100 kgs my last workout. My goal today is not to lift heavier than 100 kg, but to do more reps on that weight. I almost never add weight until I can do at least 10 reps, this is a way for me to feel “safe” and confident once I go heavier. Hope that makes sense 🤣💪🏽

node.text:
The ”post-workout glow” isn’t a myth ✨🏋🏽‍♂️ 
Yesterday's session 👇🏽 
•Single leg RDL in smith 
40 kg 12 reps x 3 sets each leg 
•Reversed barbell lunges 60 kg 10 reps x 3 sets each leg 
•Hip thrust 160 kg 3 sets until failure 
•Seated leg extension 
85 kg until failure 
90 kg until failure 
95 kg until failure 
100 kg until failure 

I am currently not super motivated(always lose my cravings for the gym when it's hot outside), so when I go I focus on exercises that I enjoy doing. The "real" work will prob start in September, when it's getting less warm outside. At the moment I am just trying to maintain my current physique, I don't really feel like pressuring myself too much right now. Honestly prioritizing my tan and the beach while our short summer lasts🇸🇪🤣🏖
